The paper discusses the optimization of parallel transmission in elastic optical networks to support high-speed Ethernet, which involves network infrastructure, communication protocols, and optimization algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with information theory and signal processing, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely sub-category. The paper focuses on optical networks and transmission, which indicates cs.OC (Optical Networking) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves system optimization and resource allocation, which suggests cs.SI (Systems and Control) as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with network performance and efficiency, which suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the fifth likely sub-category.
